"ext": "mp4", "width": 1080, "height": 1920, "tbr": 1479.056, "format_note": "DASH video", "container": "mp4_dash", "vcodec": "vp09.00.40.08.00.01.01.01.00", "acodec": "none", "dynamic_range": "SDR", "url": "https://scontent-mia3-3.cdninstagram.com/o1/v/t2/f2/m367/AQNNnrv6iuwF65QcCW4G416knY7v2AjaWGwCNlHiMRShVoU2ZLLVzsvcx9koJL3R2DQeev2I1jBhb1IGIrcarzgKrzNx7QSZS7U4ZwY.mp4?_nc_cat=109&_nc_sid=9ca052&_nc_ht=scontent-mia3-3.cdninstagram.com&_nc_ohc=Z3U1Sznqck0Q7kNvwGqk9bf&%3D%3D&ccb=17-1&_nc_gid=f4sc6JHH4g8F3aSptknSwA&_nc_zt=28&_nc_ss=7a22e&oh=00_Af45gyRQcaHdj4haxBP5erXfZMeqxcwMvqI4B13eH-zW8A&oe=6A1E430A", "manifest_stream_number": 0, "is_dash_periods": true, "protocol": "https", "video_ext": "mp4", "audio_ext": "none", "abr": 0, "vbr": 1479.056, "resolution": "1080x1920", "aspect_ratio": 0.56, "filesize_approx": 7636920, "http_headers": {"User-Agent": "Mozilla/5.0 (Windows NT 10.0; Win64; x64) AppleWebKit/537.36 (KHTML, like Gecko) Chrome/140.0.0.0 Safari/537.36", "Accept": "text/html,application/xhtml+xml,application/xml;q=0.9,*/*;q=0.8", "Accept-Language": "en-us,en;q=0.5", "Sec-Fetch-Mode": "navigate", "Referer": "https://www.instagram.com/"}, "format": "dash-1251166000306173v - 1080x1920 (DASH video)"}], "title": "Video by bilawal.ai", "description": "Comment ‘4d’ to learn how I made this. I made a 4D god’s eye replay of the Iran strikes using public OSINT data. \n\nWhen I turned on the orbital layer in worldview something jumped out.\n\nYou can see satellite passes stack up over the strike zones in the hours before & after impact. Everyone was watching. Some of them were overhead before it started.\n\nAmerican KH-11s and TOPAZ SAR. Russian BARS-M and Persona. Chinese Gaofen optical and SAR. Maxar WorldView Legion. Airbus Pleiades. Capella. ICEYE.\n\nThat’s textbook behavior — you collect right before for targeting, you strike, then you collect again for battle damage assessment. Just wild to see it all replayed in 3D like this.\n\nThe commercial constellation densi